First check container name:

docker ps

Then run:

docker exec -it <container_name> bash

Inside container:

chown -R librenms:librenms /opt/librenms
chmod -R ug=rwX /opt/librenms

Check validation:

su - librenms
./validate.php

Or directly from host:

docker exec -it <container_name> su -s /bin/bash librenms -c "./validate.php"

If RRD ownership issue still exists:

chown -R librenms:librenms /opt/librenms/rrd
chown -R librenms:librenms /opt/librenms/logs

Then restart container:

docker restart <container_name>

If using docker-compose:

docker compose restart

You can also identify wrong ownership files with:
find /opt/librenms ! -user librenms
